Food was excellent and portion sizes were very large and filling. We went in for Saturday Sunday brunch (10-2pm) and my friend got Green Chilaquiles with Carnitas and Egg and I got the Fried Chicken and Waffles Benedict. Chicken was perfect, moist on the inside and with tasty batter on the outside, and went with the waffles well. My friend really liked the Chilaquiles. Server seemed rushed even though the restaurant was less than half full, but was quick to get anything forgotten like side of syrup or drinks.  The food was so satisfying neither of us could fit dessert at the end, but the cheesecake there is amazing, so we ordered two slices to go for when we weren't as stuffed. I was disappointed in how bland the white chocolate peppermint bark cheesecake was, didn't taste like much besides a lot of crunchy minty bits where's the cheesecake? but the reason I tried a new flavor is because I love so many of TCF's flavors! I admit I usually just go for cheesecake and not a whole meal, and then the Lemon Raspberry Cream or Chocolate Mousse cheesecakes are wonderful favorites. I took a chance on the Vanilla Bean cheesecake (too many places think vanilla means tasteless) and really enjoyed it, definite vanilla flavor and the crust, mousse, and cheesecake were all distinct and great together.

Food was excellent and portion sizes were very large and filling. We went in for Saturday Sunday brunch (10-2pm) and my friend got Green Chilaquiles with Carnitas and Egg and I got the Fried Chicken and Waffles Benedict. Chicken was perfect, moist on the inside and with tasty batter on the outside, and went with the waffles well. My friend really liked the Chilaquiles. Server seemed rushed even though the restaurant was less than half full, but was quick to get anything forgotten like side of syrup or drinks.  The food was so satisfying neither of us could fit dessert at the end, but the cheesecake there is amazing, so we ordered two slices to go for when we weren't as stuffed. I was disappointed in how bland the white chocolate peppermint bark cheesecake was, didn't taste like much besides a lot of crunchy minty bits where's the cheesecake? but the reason I tried a new flavor is because I love so many of TCF's flavors! Its probably called the cheese cake factory for a reason. I had pancakes chicken and waffles and scrambled eggs with hollandaise sauce. It was ok didn't really leave a big impression in the tastebuds but I do like to be fair and try this place a couple more times to really have a just opinion about it. This experience I had here this time was mediocre at best. They did take a while to bring the food out and the syrup made my mouths dry. Idk it could have been me very I'm thinking having brunch here isn't he best idea to go with.

I ordered Shepard's pie as you can see in the picture. The worst Shepard's pie ever. Felt like I'm eating a pile of grease. Very disappointing as this is a staple for Cheesecake Factory. Do not order here again ever.  The quality has drastically gone down. I will never eat here again. No coronary for me On a lighter note. I spoke to the manager  about my food. He was very gracious and apologized for the food and allowed me to order something else. I ordered an spinach, bacon omelette with toast instead.... the omelette was very good and I was happy. I appreciate the professionalism and the prompt action by the manager. Because of him we stayed and our experience was remediated. Thank you Mr. Manager.

The hostesses were extremely friendly. The wait was longer than we were told, about 40 mins when they told us 20, but that's okay. Our waiter was John. He was so nice and very helpful with our questions. The food was good, I got a salad and it was huge. John always made sure we weren't low on water which was nice because some restaurants take forever to refill. The Cheesecake was still frozen :( which kind of ruined the greatness of the rest of the experience. But I would return to cheese cake factory

I always order my cheesecake curbside pickup; however, this evening after waiting on hold for ten minutes I was informed that pickup orders for cheesecake are not allowed. I work in the mall and only wanted to pick it up curbside. Oh AND ALL of the 15 minute curbside parking spaces were occupied by patrons who definitely were there longer than 15 minutes. A HUGE inconvenience for a restaurant whose main staple is CHEESECAKE!

I've only been here twice now and my very first experience was amazing! Everything that I ordered tasted delicious . I ordered their strawberry lemonade, Korean fried cauliflower, fish and chips, I used sweet potato cut fries instead. Everything tasted fantastic and this is definitely a go to spot. Their prices are reasonable. For four people we paid $90. But the service & quality was great.

Been here several times. Everytime is great. The waiter I had last night was very knowledgeable with the menu and nice. The crusted chicken romano is one of my favorites. Make sure you prepare wait on the weekends or arrival early. It can get really packed.
